Tuning Identificando o número de cores disponíveis ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-6_fa5a22de95791ae4e2f888ee44ab53b5'} ```{.r .cell-code} parallel::detectCores(logical = TRUE) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] 4 ``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-7_aee86513855729f00f8b5f305adfbd6e'} ```{.r .cell-code} parallel_start(4, .method = "parallel") ``` ::: ## Recipe ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-8_c29ec9e4ae44da259076bf04f10bc51b'} ```{.r .cell-code} recipe_spec_1 <- recipe(media ~ ., data = training(splits)) %>% step_timeseries_signature(mes) %>% step_rm(mes) %>% step_nzv(all_numeric_predictors()) %>% step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors()) %>% step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors(), one_hot = TRUE) recipe_spec_1 %>% prep() %>% bake(new_data=NULL) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A tibble: 117 × 37 media mes_index.num mes_year mes_year.iso mes_half mes_quarter mes_month 1 162. -1.71 -1.55 -1.55 -0.971 -1.32 -1.57 2 158. -1.68 -1.55 -1.55 -0.971 -1.32 -1.28 3 154. -1.65 -1.55 -1.55 -0.971 -1.32 -0.986 4 144. -1.62 -1.55 -1.55 -0.971 -0.416 -0.695 5 137. -1.59 -1.55 -1.55 -0.971 -0.416 -0.404 6 130. -1.56 -1.55 -1.55 -0.971 -0.416 -0.112 7 124. -1.53 -1.55 -1.55 1.02 0.485 0.179 8 131. -1.50 -1.55 -1.55 1.02 0.485 0.471 9 130. -1.47 -1.55 -1.55 1.02 0.485 0.762 10 127. -1.44 -1.55 -1.55 1.02 1.39 1.05 # ℹ 107 more rows # ℹ 30 more variables: mes_month.xts , mes_wday , mes_wday.xts , # mes_qday , mes_yday , mes_mweek , mes_week , # mes_week.iso , mes_week2 , mes_week3 , mes_week4 , # mes_month.lbl_01 , mes_month.lbl_02 , mes_month.lbl_03 , # mes_month.lbl_04 , mes_month.lbl_05 , mes_month.lbl_06 , # mes_month.lbl_07 , mes_month.lbl_08 , mes_month.lbl_09 , … ``` ::: ::: ## Model Specifications ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-9_fdc989b2a97aa6eff823ebcf970df1aa'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_tbl <- tibble( learn_rate = c(0.200, 0.300, 0.400, 0.500, 0.600, 0.700) ) %>% create_model_grid( f_model_spec = boost_tree, engine_name = "xgboost", mode = "regression" ) model_tbl ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A tibble: 6 × 2 learn_rate .models 1 0.2 2 0.3 3 0.4 4 0.5 5 0.6 6 0.7 ``` ::: ::: ##Extracting the model list ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-10_7634154b870a6672ac21c713c3db1bc9'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_list <- model_tbl$.models model_list ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [[1]] Boosted Tree Model Specification (regression) Main Arguments: learn_rate = 0.2 Computational engine: xgboost [[2]] Boosted Tree Model Specification (regression) Main Arguments: learn_rate = 0.3 Computational engine: xgboost [[3]] Boosted Tree Model Specification (regression) Main Arguments: learn_rate = 0.4 Computational engine: xgboost [[4]] Boosted Tree Model Specification (regression) Main Arguments: learn_rate = 0.5 Computational engine: xgboost [[5]] Boosted Tree Model Specification (regression) Main Arguments: learn_rate = 0.6 Computational engine: xgboost [[6]] Boosted Tree Model Specification (regression) Main Arguments: learn_rate = 0.7 Computational engine: xgboost ``` ::: ::: ## Workflowsets ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-11_e0edc75fa3403fb7deed50f2a283ed00'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_wfset <- workflow_set( preproc = list( recipe_spec_1 ), models = model_list, cross = TRUE ) model_wfset ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A workflow set/tibble: 6 × 4 wflow_id info option result 1 recipe_boost_tree_1 2 recipe_boost_tree_2 3 recipe_boost_tree_3 4 recipe_boost_tree_4 5 recipe_boost_tree_5 6 recipe_boost_tree_6 ``` ::: ::: ## Parallel Training (Fitting) ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-12_4ee36cd4f981a6fb9a869160564203d6'} ```{.r .cell-code} control_fit_workflowset( verbose = TRUE, allow_par = TRUE ) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` workflowset control object -------------------------- allow_par : TRUE cores : 4 verbose : TRUE packages : modeltime parsnip workflows dplyr stats lubridate tidymodels timetk rsample recipes yardstick dials tune xgboost workflowsets modeldata infer scales broom tidyquant quantmod TTR PerformanceAnalytics xts zoo forcats stringr purrr readr tidyr tibble ggplot2 tidyverse graphics grDevices utils datasets methods base ``` ::: ::: ## Fitting Using Parallel Backend ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-13_d25a839f8f5eb12c57af0f0ef07a33d5'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_parallel_tbl <- model_wfset %>% modeltime_fit_workflowset( data = training(splits), control = control_fit_workflowset( verbose = TRUE, allow_par = TRUE ) ) ``` ::: ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-14_ea4cfa37f12e0e0d6da47126e4b1fc3e'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_parallel_tbl ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # Modeltime Table # A tibble: 6 × 3 .model_id .model .model_desc 1 1 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_1 2 2 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_2 3 3 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_3 4 4 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_4 5 5 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_5 6 6 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_6 ``` ::: ::: ## Comparison to Sequential Backend ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-15_abdfed20fb332f246e1ea41adafa30e0'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_sequential_tbl <- model_wfset %>% modeltime_fit_workflowset( data = training(splits), control = control_fit_workflowset( verbose = TRUE, allow_par = FALSE ) ) ``` ::: ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-16_e1d03b7835db3e3abee730a8ce1936d2'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_parallel_tbl %>% modeltime_calibrate(testing(splits)) %>% modeltime_accuracy() #%>% ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` # A tibble: 6 × 9 .model_id .model_desc .type mae mape mase smape rmse rsq 1 1 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_1 Test 21.6 12.1 4.75 13.0 23.2 0.293 2 2 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_2 Test 18.3 10.2 4.03 10.9 20.1 0.259 3 3 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_3 Test 17.9 10.0 3.95 10.7 19.9 0.109 4 4 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_4 Test 16.8 9.40 3.71 9.97 18.8 0.00773 5 5 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_5 Test 22.0 12.3 4.84 13.3 23.9 0.00238 6 6 RECIPE_BOOST_TREE_6 Test 16.5 9.26 3.63 9.79 17.9 0.223 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # table_modeltime_accuracy(.interactive = FALSE) ``` ::: ## Forecast Assessment ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-17_c18cc3f6ebc1a0e9e875e348425e3fd0'} ```{.r .cell-code} model_parallel_tbl %>% modeltime_calibrate(testing(splits)) %>% modeltime_forecast( new_data = testing(splits), actual_data = gold_mean, keep_data = TRUE ) %>% plot_modeltime_forecast() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: fazer o tuning dos dois parâmetros separados e contruir um modelo com eles para ver como fica ## Forecast future ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-18_da9545b701a37e4c25c3ec7cd6f0b39f'} ```{.r .cell-code} future_forecast_tbl <- model_parallel_tbl %>% modeltime_calibrate(testing(splits)) %>% modeltime_refit(gold_mean) %>% modeltime_forecast( h = "1 year", actual_data = gold_mean ) ``` ::: ::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-19_cc681346b56b8769ca67b7bd35af91fb'} ```{.r .cell-code} future_forecast_tbl %>% plot_modeltime_forecast() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
